'''
Indexing in Python*:

Indexing means accessing individual elements of a sequence (like a string, list, or tuple) using their position.

Types of Indexing:
1.Positive Indexing: Starts from 0  
2.Negative Indexing: Starts from -1 (last element)

Examples:

List
fruits = ['apple', 'banana', 'cherry']
#Positive indexing
print(fruits[0])   # apple
print(fruits[2])   # cherry

#Negative indexing
print(fruits[-1])  # cherry
print(fruits[-2])  # banana

text = "Python"

print(text[0])   # P
print(text[-1])  # n
'''

# Simple Indexing Program in Python
text = input("Enter any text: ")

print("First character:", text[0])
print("Last character:", text[-1])
print("Third character:", text[2])

#Index 1 to 4 characters
print("Characters from index 1 to 4:", text[1:5])
